                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>July 17th&#47;89<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93; you will<lb/> please excuse me for neglecting thus far to<lb/> communicate to you the results<lb/> of my trip to Boston&#44; but I<lb/> have been exceedingly busy and<lb/> expected perhaps to see you in N. Y<lb/> at one of the lectures and so<lb/> deferred writing from day to<lb/> day.  The results were not very<lb/> great&#44; not because such results<lb/> are not to be obtained but be&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>cause I could not take sufficient<lb/> time to do the work thoroughly.<lb/>  I was only in Boston three days<lb/> and a half&#44; including Sabbath&#44;<lb/> but I managed to see the<lb/> Presidents and ministers of the<lb/> Union Park&#44; Ash&#44; Pleasant and<lb/> Hanover st congregations&#44; who<lb/> all promised me their assistance<lb/> and endeavors in inducing their<lb/> congregations to join.  I obtained<lb/> a few subscriptions from individuals<lb/> and if properly asked&#44; there is no<lb/> doubt but that many such could be<lb/> obtained in Boston.  Mr Marcus<lb/> would not do anything for the<lb/> Seminary though he promised<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>help for my proposed synagogue.<lb/>  His reasons you are acquainted<lb/> with.  The lectures have been<lb/> regularly continued here with fair<lb/> success.  Last <sic>sunday</sic> I spoke &#38;<lb/> for next Sunday Dr H. P. Mendes is<lb/> on the list.  I remain&#44; with best<lb/> regards<lb/> yours truly<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
                
            <p>P. S.  We have not heard from<lb/> Mr Sulzberger for some time.  Accord&#45;<lb/>&#45;ing to the last reports he was<lb/> intending to return to America<lb/> after the fall holidays<lb/> B. D.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>From<lb/>
                B. Drachman<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">329 E. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> St N. Y</hi><lb/></p>
            
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5th St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
